Brigida, the leader of this group, is a 47-year old woman and a single mother of 5 children.  She’s been selling clothing in her community for 15 years.  During all this time, that business has been the principal source of income of her family.  Brigida personifies this class of women, living in very humble conditions, but who challenged to make a change in their families by their own, thanks to their hard works.  The entrepreneur explains that in the beginning it was really hard to capture the clients and have good sales volume.  She had to walk all day long visiting people in the neighborhood to promote her goods.  Her strategy had very good results, and now her business is well-known in the community.
In addition of clothing, Brigida sells toys during the Christmas period.  This loan is to buy new clothing to add to her inventory.  She’ll also seize the opportunity to buy some toys to sell in the neighborhood.
Brigida is joined in her group by:
Altagarcia O. P., who sells beauty products;
Emilia O., an old woman that sells fried dishes;
Ocalia P. S., who sells garments;
Dermis A. F., who sells women’s clothing;
The picture shows from left to right, Brigida, Altagarcia, Emilia, Ocalia and Dermis.
